{
  "texts": [
    "One widely used method for oversampling the minority class is the Adaptive synthetic sampling approach for imbalanced learning (ADASYN) 64, 65.",
    "ADASYN uses a weighted distribution that considers the learning difficulties of distinct instances within the minority class, generating more synthetic data for challenging instances and fewer for less challenging ones 66.",
    "To address potential overgeneralization in SMOTE 56, 61, Borderline-SMOTE is proposed.",
    "It concentrates on minority samples that are close to the decision boundary between classes.",
    "These samples are considered to be more informative for improving the performance of the classification model on the minority class."
  ]
}